verbose_text: Humins are thought to form by the condensation of intermediate sugars and aldehydes.23, 24 Similarly, low molecular weight carbohydrates in ChCl / oxalic acid DES were almost completely transformed (total conversion to product of 96, 97, and 99% for cellobiose, glucose, and fructose, respectively, Table S1) into a bulk of undesirable humins and small amounts of HMF (yields up to 11 mol%).
